metadata.name: Forty Six & Two
metadata.description:
Inspired by the song of the same name by Tool.

Exploring a proposition concerning the possibility of reaching a state of evolution at which the body would have two more than the normal 46 total chromosomes and leave the disharmonious state behind.

The next step of evolution would likely result in human DNA being reorganized into 46 autosomes and two sex chromosomes.

There is no telling how that form could come to life, but however it may be, harmony, balance and structure would be at its core.
